    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-06T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="779"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.20/152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-06T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 6, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>258. Your 315, February 18, 6 p.m.<note n="51" xml:id="d779fn51">Not
                        printed.</note> Navy Department states that during the recent visits to
                    Valparaiso of Rear Admiral Whiting he conferred with the Chief of the General
                    Staff of the Chilean Navy<note n="52" xml:id="d779fn52">Adm. Julio Allard
                        Pinto.</note> and reached several agreements for cooperative action. These
                    agreements provide for the designation of an American liaison officer with the
                    General Staff and for two Chilean Naval Officers to be received on vessels of
                    the Southeast Pacific Force.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
